modules.description: Provides functions for establishing MQTT connections, publishing messages, and subscribing to topics. Operates with data types such as client identifiers, topic strings, and message payloads. Used to integrate real-time messaging in IoT applications or event-driven systems.

Establishes and manages MQTT connections, handles message publishing, and subscribes to topics with specified quality of service. Operates on client instances, credentials, and quality-of-service levels. Used to connect to brokers, send messages to topics, and receive messages from subscribed topics in real-time.
